{"type":"message","id":"97137ffb","parentId":"497cb424","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:01:09.154Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_1e22c7dc-5729-44c8-b8d7-0abda261eeca","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0e804f62.txt\n143f2fb3.txt\n2026-03-24_nursesphere_international_nurse_recruitment.md\n2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md\n2026-04-06_tiny_manyonga_personal_post.md\n270eafe2.txt\n361e6e45.txt\n4ded931f.txt\n5e89417c.txt\n86f96fdc.txt\n8aa88596.txt\n8d171cfe.txt\n8f1be070.txt\n92b658ec.txt\nb2902a80.txt\nc633d5fe.txt\nd12f23f8.txt\nd3f60f4a.txt\nd9011790.txt\ne0cde359.txt\nf4d187b6.txt"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"0e804f62.txt\n143f2fb3.txt\n2026-03-24_nursesphere_international_nurse_recruitment.md\n2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md\n2026-04-06_tiny_manyonga_personal_post.md\n270eafe2.txt\n361e6e45.txt\n4ded931f.txt\n5e89417c.txt\n86f96fdc.txt\n8aa88596.txt\n8d171cfe.txt\n8f1be070.txt\n92b658ec.txt\nb2902a80.txt\nc633d5fe.txt\nd12f23f8.txt\nd3f60f4a.txt\nd9011790.txt\ne0cde359.txt\nf4d187b6.txt","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776060069153}}
{"type":"message","id":"56d3e163","parentId":"97137ffb","timestamp":"2026-04-13T06:01:09.168Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_ebf3ec68-7f45-4680-9070-579554c0fc97","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 0e804f62.txt ===\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\nBuilt with passion.  Backed by\nExperience.\n\n=== 143f2fb3.txt ===\nSpecialized Healthcare Staffing Solutions for Long-Term Care & Assisted Living Facilities\nRunning a long-term care or assisted living facility means juggling resident needs, staff well-being, regulatory demands, and family expectations all at once. The pressure is constant, and the stakes are deeply personal. Residents depend on consistency. Families expect compassion. Your team needs the support to deliver both.\nAt Nava Healthcare, Our origin story started out of the dire needs we personally experienced while operating in this industry, and therefore we work closely with administrators and facility leaders to provide staff who bring the right mix of experience, reliability, and empathy. From floor nurses and CNAs to clinical leadership and support staff, we help you maintain stable coverage without compromising the continuity your residents deserve.\n\n=== 2026-03-24_nursesphere_international_nurse_recruitment.md ===\n# **International Nurse Recruitment: How NurseSphere™ Ends the 13-Week Travel Nurse Cycle**\n\nThe American healthcare system is currently navigating a zero-ROI loop. This loop threatens both clinical outcomes and fiscal solvency. For years, facility leaders have relied on travel nursing as a vital pressure valve, a way to ensure shift coverage in an increasingly volatile labor market. However, what began as a short-term solution has metastasized into a structural dependency that erodes team culture and drains capital. The 13-week contract, once a tool for agility, has become a symbol of the transactional fallacy, where availability is prioritized over adaptability. To break this cycle, health systems must pivot from reactive domestic firefighting to a proactive, scalable strategy. This is the mandate of NurseSphere™: an international nurse recruitment blueprint designed not just to fill holes, but to build permanent, high-retention workforces in a single hiring cycle.\n\n=== 2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md ===\nSource: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nava-healthcare-recruitment-67170741/\nTitle: Eight patients. One CNA. In a rehab unit, that would be a typical Tuesday, but in an oncology unit? That's a crisis.\nAuthor: Nava Healthcare Recruitment (Corporate)\n\n=== 2026-04-06_tiny_manyonga_personal_post.md ===\n# Tiny Manyonga Personal Post — Apr 6, 2026\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga (personal)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"=== 0e804f62.txt ===\nNava Healthcare Recruitment\nBuilt with passion.  Backed by\nExperience.\n\n=== 143f2fb3.txt ===\nSpecialized Healthcare Staffing Solutions for Long-Term Care & Assisted Living Facilities\nRunning a long-term care or assisted living facility means juggling resident needs, staff well-being, regulatory demands, and family expectations all at once. The pressure is constant, and the stakes are deeply personal. Residents depend on consistency. Families expect compassion. Your team needs the support to deliver both.\nAt Nava Healthcare, Our origin story started out of the dire needs we personally experienced while operating in this industry, and therefore we work closely with administrators and facility leaders to provide staff who bring the right mix of experience, reliability, and empathy. From floor nurses and CNAs to clinical leadership and support staff, we help you maintain stable coverage without compromising the continuity your residents deserve.\n\n=== 2026-03-24_nursesphere_international_nurse_recruitment.md ===\n# **International Nurse Recruitment: How NurseSphere™ Ends the 13-Week Travel Nurse Cycle**\n\nThe American healthcare system is currently navigating a zero-ROI loop. This loop threatens both clinical outcomes and fiscal solvency. For years, facility leaders have relied on travel nursing as a vital pressure valve, a way to ensure shift coverage in an increasingly volatile labor market. However, what began as a short-term solution has metastasized into a structural dependency that erodes team culture and drains capital. The 13-week contract, once a tool for agility, has become a symbol of the transactional fallacy, where availability is prioritized over adaptability. To break this cycle, health systems must pivot from reactive domestic firefighting to a proactive, scalable strategy. This is the mandate of NurseSphere™: an international nurse recruitment blueprint designed not just to fill holes, but to build permanent, high-retention workforces in a single hiring cycle.\n\n=== 2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md ===\nSource: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nava-healthcare-recruitment-67170741/\nTitle: Eight patients. One CNA. In a rehab unit, that would be a typical Tuesday, but in an oncology unit? That's a crisis.\nAuthor: Nava Healthcare Recruitment (Corporate)\n\n=== 2026-04-06_tiny_manyonga_personal_post.md ===\n# Tiny Manyonga Personal Post — Apr 6, 2026\n\n**Author:** Tiny Manyonga (personal)","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776060069166}}
